def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    """Returns priority with which we want to add item to each bin.

    Args:
        item: Size of item to be added to the bin.
        bins: Array of capacities for each bin.

    Return:
        Array of same size as bins with priority score of each bin.
    """
    priorities = np.zeros_like(bins)  # Initialize array to store priorities

    for i in range(len(bins)):
        if bins[i] == 0:  # If the bin has no capacity, prioritize it the lowest
            priorities[i] = 0
        elif item <= bins[i]:  # If item can fit in the bin
            if (bins[i] - item) / bins[i] >= 0.5:  # If remaining space is more than 50% of bin capacity
                priorities[i] = 1 + item / bins[i]  # Priority is 1 + ratio of item to bin capacity
            else:
                priorities[i] = 1.5 + (item - bins[i]) / bins[i]  # Priority is 1.5 plus ratio of remaining item to bin capacity
        else:
            priorities[i] = 1 - (item - bins[i]) / item  # Priority is 1 minus ratio of remaining item to total item

    return priorities
